      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZAMBORA BLISS (3) comes off a big run when third in a quick 34.04 at Sandown over 595m. Has the ability and expected to go close again. OUTSIDES (1) jumped from this box last time and placed in a Grade 5 at Geelong over 680m, finishing second (39.42). Has a very consistent record off this same box, including three wins and six placings from 11 starts. Must include in calculations. PAW IKE (2) tends to take a while to wind up, running on to place two back before spotting a start latest and finishing on strongly into third (34.71) in a Grade 4/5 at this track. Has a good record here including six wins. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Overdue and is among the main hopes. MAGIC LOKI (8) profiles nicely over this trip.",
